title: Queen's Day Criterium
description:
Wake up and smell the tulips! While you\'re at it, check your season readiness at this early season criterium. A revival of the popular old Holland Classic, this scenic course promises to be flat and fast while offering plenty of spectator amenities.

Not familiar with the Queen\'s Day celebration? The Dutch people celebrate the birthday of Queen Beatrix on April 30th by wearing orange and having fun! We thought the best way to celebrate Queen\'s Day here in Holland was with a cycling event tying us in even tighter with our Dutch roots, so we brought back a criterium to Downtown Holland.
course: The flat and fast course is a unique \"figure 8\". Starting in front of the Knickerbocker Theater on 8th Street in downtown Holland, racers head west 8th. The course continues with a turn south on College, west on 7th, north on Central, east on 8th, north on College, east on 9th, south on Columbia and east on 8th, and back to the start/finish in front of the theater.
registration:
Juniors: $15 
Men\'s & Women\'s Cat 1-5 $30 through 4/26; $45 on race day
Multiple Race: Additional $20

Gran Fondo di Thumb
description:
“Gran Fondo” means “Big Ride” in Italian.  They are long distance, mass-participation cycling events – not races – that have become immensely popular in Europe.  In France they’re known as “cyclosportives”.  participation is open to recreational and competitive amateur cyclists and tens of thousands of riders of all abilities participate.

Gran Fondos are often named after famous cyclists of the past or after companies with a long heritage in cycling.  Some of the most famous Gran Fondos include the Prosecco Classic, The Nove Colli and the Felice Gimondi.

Wind Turbines of Ubly  and  Native American Petroglpyh’s  are  the highlights of the Double Metric Century course.

Mass Start time at 8 a.m.

No USA Cycling license required.

A helmet is required

The Gran Fondo  rides all  start  at Zehnders park  which is  730 S. Main Street   Frankenmuth, MI  48734

However, if you want to start your ride at one of the first two rest stops, you may. However, you must first pick up your bib number at the registration table  in Frankenmuth.  If desired, you can pick up your bib number Friday night or Saturday. You can choose your preferred starting point, but that means ya gotta drive to get there and back.  There is no parking available at the third rest stop.
course:
40 miles - to 1st Rest stop  - GILFORD RD TOWNSHIP HALL  -  ( Water, Heed mix   and porta john available) then back  to  Frankenmuth.  This rest stop is open from 8:30 a.m. till 3 p.m.  all riders must be already be on the way back to Frankenmuth  by  3 p.m.

65 miles -  to  2nd Rest stop –  VILLAGE OF AKRON-  (   Main Lunch is here   water, sandwiches, porta johns available ) then  back to Frankenmuth this course is relatively flat. This rest stop is open from 8:30  a.m. till 2 p.m.  all riders must be already be on the way back to Frankenmuth  by  3 p.m. See map: http://www.mapmyride.com/view_route?r=926126960809080524
registration:
https://www.truesport.com/index.php/events/truesport_event/88
If you volunteer at the Tour de Frankemuth bike race the day before this event, you receive free entry into this event.  If you race in the Tour de Frankemuth bike race, you receive a $10 off coupon.
directions: The event starts in front of the Zehnder\'s restaurant, 730 S MAIN ST, Frankemuth MI 48734.

title: Big Bad Wolf Cyclocross Race
description: This race will be held at Stratford Woods Park in Midland, MI.  The race is being presented by Revolution Racing Cycling team, Midland Brewing Company and Cyclefit Multisport.  Our races are designed to imcrease awareness and participation in all cycling events in Michigan. We encourage anyone to come try out the exciting sport of Cyclocross.
course: The 2012 course was hailed as one of the most challenging and technical courses of the entire Michigan racing calendar.  The course was labeled as the most European style course in the state and was even said that "Belgiums would be proud."  We utilize the features of the park to provide the best experience with sand, more sand, water, hills, trails and trees.
registration: All USACycling rules and regulations apply.  Riders must use a helmet.  A ONE-DAY or ANNUAL license is required to race. These can be purchased at usacycling.org or on the day of the event.
notes: Online Registration will close prior to the day of the event.  You will be able to register and purchase licenses on the day of the event in person.  Registration opens at 8am and will close 30 min before each race.
directions: Park Entrance off of Ashman Street.  From the South, follow US 10 and business 10 in to midland.  Take first exit to Patrick Road and head North on Waldo Rd. Turn East on Ashman and South into park entrance.
